```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>3x3 Grid with Dropdown</title>
    <style>
        body {
            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
            margin: 0;
            padding: 20px;
        }

        select {
            margin-bottom: 20px;
            padding: 10px;
            font-size: 16px;
        }

        .grid {
            display: grid;
            grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
            gap: 10px;
        }

        .cell {
            aspect-ratio: 3 / 2;
            background-color: #f0f0f0;
            display: flex;
            justify-content: center;
            align-items: center;
            overflow: hidden;
        }

        .cell img {
            width: 100%;
            height: 100%;
            object-fit: cover;
        }
    </style>
</head>

<body>

    <select id="channelSelect">
        <option value="">Select a channel</option>
        <!-- Generate options dynamically -->
        <script>
            for (let i = 1; i <= 23; i++) {
                document.write(`<option value="channel${i}">Channel ${i}</option>`);
            }
        </script>
    </select>

    <div class="grid" id="imageGrid">
        <!-- Generate grid cells dynamically -->
        <script>
            for (let i = 0; i < 9; i++) {
                document.write('<div class="cell"><img src="https://picsum.photos/300/200" alt="Thumbnail"></div>');
            }
        </script>
    </div>

    <script>
        const selectElement = document.getElementById('channelSelect');
        const imageCells = document.querySelectorAll('.cell img');

        selectElement.addEventListener('change', function () {
            // Clear image cache and load new images
            imageCells.forEach(img => {
                img.src = `https://picsum.photos/300/200?random=${Math.random()}`;
            });
        });
    </script>

</body>

</html>
``` 

**Explanation:**

- **HTML Structure**: The document contains a dropdown menu and a grid of images.

- **CSS Styles**: The grid is styled to have a 3x3 layout with a 3:2 aspect ratio for each cell.

- **JavaScript Functionality**: 
  - The dropdown menu is populated with 23 options labeled "Channel 1" to "Channel 23".
  - When a new selection is made, the images in the grid are refreshed with new images from the specified URL, ensuring that the cache is cleared by appending a random query parameter.
